title: Rally for rescue dog 'tortured and killed' by elderly couple
text:
Rally for rescue dog 'tortured and killed' by elderly couple By Associated Press Protesters gathered in the Lithuanian village. (Facebook) 
Dozens of people have protested in a small Lithuanian village against the slaying of a dog that police say an elderly couple adopted, tortured and then killed. 
Protesters with banners and a painted portrait of the dog named Moby shouted "Murderers!" as they gathered outside the suspects' house, where the three-year-old mixed breed male dog was reportedly killed last week. 
The couple, who has not been named, was charged with animal cruelty. Their lawyer was not available for comment yesterday. 
Ilma Germaniene, head of the shelter where Moby was placed in December after his owner died, said yesterday's rally was "to make sure no more dogs will be slaughtered". 
Moby was adopted mid-last month from the shelter in Sventupe, a village 80km north of the capital of Vilnius. Protesters gathered in the Lithuanian village. (Facebook) Â© Nine Digital Pty Ltd 2017
